Political Capital: Hungarian Guard increased risk country
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital (Risk Analysing Division), the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed last August, with the support of Jobbik Magyarorsz-gerity Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary) is increasing in several respects the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its “risk warning”, the company states that, in connection with the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that “a short-term aggressive ethnic clashes can occur as a result of the worsening of the already existing ethnic tension between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population of Hungary”.
The research institute added that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy likely to provoke this situation is the main reason.
As they say, this is due to one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: "public actors have gone through the public debate on the matter of the Roma to representatives of the radical and extreme political groupings that have based a political strategy on the dispute between the Gypsies and the Hungarians".
The problem is compounded, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are being strengthened and aggressive conflicts are more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, as a result of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media, the activity of the Hungarian Guard “significantly damaged Hungary's image abroad, in particular with regard to the confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country”.
