The Department of Health will have to carry out pre-employment checks on overseas personnel, to be sure of the validity of their qualifications, experience and work permits for the United Kingdom.
Although the Scottish Department of Health uses the Scottish Disclosure to carry out the checks on previous criminal proceedings, the agency has no right to obtain such information outside Britain.
Among the many warnings, the Auditor General's report now states that the committees are required to deal with the Office for the Monitoring of Criminal Preferentials, thus allowing employers to undertake controls on various countries.
“Although we have discovered that some personnel information has been verified, this is not done every time,” the report says.
